<section class="farm-faq">

  <div class="farm-faq__hero">
    <p class="farm-faq__eyebrow">Customer Information</p>
    <h1>Visit, Pickup & Gift Order FAQ</h1>
    <p>
      Clear information for customers before they visit, place a pickup order,
      or purchase a Farm Store gift basket or gift box.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="farm-faq__content">

    <div class="farm-faq__intro-card">
      <h2>Everything customers need before buying.</h2>
      <p>
        This page supports a smoother Farm Store customer journey by making
        store location, hours, pickup details, gift order expectations, shipping
        limits, and contact information easier to find.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="farm-faq__section">
      <p class="farm-faq__section-label">Store Information</p>

      <details open>
        <summary>Where is the Farm Store located?</summary>
        <p>
          The Cal Poly Pomona Farm Store is located at:
          <br><br>
          <strong>4102 S University Dr<br>
          Pomona, CA 91768</strong>
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>What are the store hours?</summary>
        <p>
          Store hours may change based on season, staffing, campus schedule,
          holidays, and product availability. Customers should check the current
          Farm Store website, Google listing, or social media before visiting.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>What does the Farm Store sell?</summary>
        <p>
          The Farm Store offers fresh produce, local goods, dairy products,
          pantry staples, seasonal items, gift products, and campus-connected
          Farm Store favorites.
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>

    <div class="farm-faq__section">
      <p class="farm-faq__section-label">Pickup Information</p>

      <details open>
        <summary>How does pickup work?</summary>
        <p>
          Select products and gift orders may be available for pickup. Customers
          should review pickup details before arriving and wait for confirmation
          that the order is ready.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>How long does it take for gift orders to be ready?</summary>
        <p>
          Gift baskets and gift boxes may require at least
          <strong>1–2 business days</strong> to prepare. Some orders may take
          longer depending on inventory, seasonality, and staff preparation time.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Can I request a pickup date?</summary>
        <p>
          Yes. Customers can provide a desired pickup date when ordering gift
          products. The Farm Store may contact the customer if the requested
          date needs to be adjusted.
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>

    <div class="farm-faq__section">
      <p class="farm-faq__section-label">Gift Baskets & Gift Boxes</p>

      <details open>
        <summary>Can I add a card message?</summary>
        <p>
          Yes. Gift products can include a card message so customers can
          personalize the order for the recipient.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Can I request specific items?</summary>
        <p>
          Customers may request specific items in the notes field, but requests
          are not guaranteed. Item availability depends on current inventory and
          seasonal supply.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Are all gift items guaranteed?</summary>
        <p>
          No. Items in gift baskets and gift boxes are based on inventory and
          are subject to possible substitutions. The Farm Store will aim to keep
          substitutions similar in value and quality.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Can I include allergy notes?</summary>
        <p>
          Yes. Customers should include allergy notes or special concerns when
          placing the order so staff can review the request.
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>

    <div class="farm-faq__section">
      <p class="farm-faq__section-label">Shipping</p>

      <details open>
        <summary>Can gift baskets be shipped?</summary>
        <p>
          Gift baskets cannot be shipped. They are intended for local pickup only.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Can gift boxes be shipped?</summary>
        <p>
          Some gift boxes may be eligible for shipping. Shipping may need to be
          calculated after the order is reviewed, and the Farm Store may contact
          the customer with the final total.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Do you ship to PO Boxes?</summary>
        <p>
          No. The Farm Store does not ship to PO Boxes.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>How are produce boxes shipped?</summary>
        <p>
          Boxes that include produce may require next-day or second-day shipping
          to maintain freshness. Saturday guarantee fees may apply if requested
          or required.
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>

    <div class="farm-faq__section">
      <p class="farm-faq__section-label">Returns, Exchanges & Support</p>

      <details open>
        <summary>Can perishable items be returned?</summary>
        <p>
          Perishable items may not be eligible for return. Customers should
          contact the Farm Store directly if an item is missing, damaged, or
          incorrect.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>What if there is a problem with my order?</summary>
        <p>
          Customers should contact the Farm Store as soon as possible with their
          name, order details, and a description of the issue.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>How can customers contact the store?</summary>
        <p>
          Customers should use the contact information listed on the Farm Store
          website, order confirmation, Google listing, or official store page.
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>

    <div class="farm-faq__story">
      <p class="farm-faq__section-label">About the Farm Store</p>
      <h2>Rooted in Cal Poly Pomona agriculture.</h2>
      <p>
        The Farm Store connects the campus and surrounding community with fresh
        produce, local goods, pantry staples, dairy products, and seasonal items.
        This FAQ page helps customers move more smoothly from discovery to
        purchase, pickup, and post-purchase support.
      </p>

      <a href="/collections/all" class="farm-faq__button">
        Browse Products
      </a>
    </div>

  </div>

</section>

